  - "benchmarking"
  - "score extraction"
  - "unsloth"
abstract: >
  fsvlm is a fully open-source benchmarking framework for vision-language models in the
  few-shot anomaly-detection setting. It provides an end-to-end pipeline — SAM-assisted
  interactive labeling, QLoRA fine-tuning (built on unsloth), tiered zero-shot / few-shot /
  full-train evaluation, and a token-logit-probability score extractor — plus reproducible
  benchmarks on MVTec AD, VisA, and DeepPCB. Released under the Apache 2.0 License for
  both research and commercial use; citation appreciated for academic work.
